import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Devmool"
	description="Real code, real builds, real bugs — across the stack. Documenting what I ship, what breaks, and what I learn."
	pubDate={new Date('May 21 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Devmool is where I document everything I build — AI agents, full-stack apps, distributed
		systems, and the failures that taught me how production actually works.
	</p>

	<p>
		Most tutorials online stop where the real problems begin. The toy demo runs on localhost,
		gets a thumbs-up, and the tutorial ends. But anyone who's shipped to production knows that's
		where it gets interesting — the DNS errors, the race conditions, the parallel run logs that
		don't make sense, the "why is this OCR returning gibberish" moments at 2 AM.
	</p>

	<p>
		So I started filming all of it. The architecture decisions. The bugs that took me three
		days to find. The fixes that finally worked. Across AI, system design, full-stack
		engineering, and everything in between.
	</p>

	<h2>What you'll find here</h2>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>AI engineering:</strong> LangGraph agents, RAG pipelines, Document AI, evals</li>
		<li><strong>System design:</strong> real architectures, not whiteboard fairy tales</li>
		<li><strong>Full-stack builds:</strong> Python, FastAPI, React, Postgres, AWS</li>
		<li><strong>Distributed systems:</strong> queues, microservices, the messy middle</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>
		Every post here has a video version on <a href="https://youtube.com/@thedevmool">YouTube</a>
		and the full working code on <a href="https://github.com/thedevmool">GitHub</a>. New post
		every 2 weeks. Hinglish-friendly. Code-first. No fluff.
	</p>

	<h2>Who this is for</h2>

	<p>
		Devs who'd rather watch someone actually build something than sit through another "Top 10 AI
		Tools" video. Engineers who want to see the messy middle of shipping, not just the polished
		end result. Anyone learning by building — not by collecting tutorials.
	</p>

	<p>
		If that's you, <a href="/blog">start with the latest posts</a> or
		<a href="https://youtube.com/@thedevmool">subscribe on YouTube</a>. New here every two weeks.
	</p>

	<hr />

	<p>
		<em>Devmool is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and hosted on GitHub
		Pages. The whole site is <a href="https://github.com/thedevmool/thedevmool.github.io">open
		source</a> — if you spot a bug or typo, send a PR.</em>
	</p>
</Layout>
